						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Kulōttuṅga-chōḷadēva III</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanavīra-dēva Year 40 = 1217-18 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is incomplete. It describes the king as one ‘who was pleased to take Madurai, Īḻam, Karuvūr and the crowned head of the Pāṇḍya, and ‘who had a hero’s and a victor's coronation’. It records an order of a certain Nandipaṉmaṉ and mentions Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam.</p>						

